trans-unit.source: Stores DPI information from which a <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Visual"></xref> or <xref href="System.Windows.UIElement"></xref> is rendered.
trans-unit.target: Lagrer ppt informasjon fra som en <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Visual"> </xref> eller <xref href="System.Windows.UIElement"> </xref> gjengis.

trans-unit.source: Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.DpiScale"></xref> structure.
trans-unit.target: Initialiserer en ny forekomst av den <xref href="System.Windows.DpiScale"> </xref> struktur.

trans-unit.source: The DPI scale on the X axis.
The DPI scale on the Y axis.
Gets the DPI scale on the X axis.
For example, if the DPI is 120 , DpiScaleX would be 1.25 (120/96).
trans-unit.target: For eksempel hvis PPT 120, DpiScaleX være 1,25 (120/96).

trans-unit.source: The DPI scale for the X axis.
Gets the DPI scale on the Yaxis.
DpiScaleY is always equal to the DpiScaleX, but still, the values are stored in separate properties.
trans-unit.target: DpiScaleY er alltid det samme som DpiScaleX, men fortsatt, verdiene er lagret i egen egenskaper.

trans-unit.source: The DPI scale for the Y axis.
Get or sets the PixelsPerDip at which the text should be rendered.
trans-unit.target: Får eller angir PixelsPerDip teksten skal gjengis.

trans-unit.source: Gets the DPI along X axis.
PixelsPerInchX and <xref:System.Windows.DpiScale.PixelsPerInchY%2A> reference the number of pixels that are drawn within an inch on the screen.
trans-unit.target: PixelsPerInchX og <xref:System.Windows.DpiScale.PixelsPerInchY%2A>Referansenummer piksler tegnes i en tomme på skjermen.</xref:System.Windows.DpiScale.PixelsPerInchY%2A>

trans-unit.source: The DPI along the X axis.
Gets the DPI along Y axis.
<xref:System.Windows.DpiScale.PixelsPerInchX%2A> and PixelsPerInchY reference the number of pixels that are drawn within an inch on the screen.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Windows.DpiScale.PixelsPerInchX%2A>og PixelsPerInchY til antall piksler tegnes i en tomme på skjermen.</xref:System.Windows.DpiScale.PixelsPerInchX%2A>

trans-unit.source: The DPI along the Y axis.
